OL,6,FThe offences were dealt with by way of
OL,7,FTraffic Offence Reports and summons.
OL,8,FThese can potentially result in a fine
OL,9,Fof #100 for failing to wear a
OL,10,Fseatbelt, #200 and six penalty points
OL,11,Ffor using a handheld mobile device and
OL,12,Fa #300 fine for driving a vehicle in
OL,13,Fcontravention of a prohibition.
OL,15,FPenalties for driving whilst
OL,16,Fdisqualified can lead to a fine of up
OL,17,Fto #5,000 and up to six months'
OL,18,Fimprisonment.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/7
